  azure_blob_storage disk + a 'tiered' storage policy (see the storage.*.example
  files in the bifract repo's clickhouse/config.d/ directory), supply the
  credentials as env vars on the clickhouse service, and set
  BIFRACT_COLD_STORAGE_BACKEND=s3 (or azure) on the bifract app.

  The 'tiered' policy MUST keep the existing 'default' disk as the 'hot' volume.
